se to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger de COURTRAI was born in 1175, in Kortrijk, West Flanders, Belgium, his father, Roger de Courtrai de Gand, was 25 and his mother, Beatrix de Nevele, was 30. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Marguerite de GUINES. He died in 1232, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1175–1232":"1175–1232","1180–1215":"1180–1215","–Male":"Surnud","1200–Female":"1200–Surnud","1197–1264":"1197–1264","1225–Male":"1225–Surnud","1150–1187":"1150–1187","1145–1186":"1145–1186","1187":"1187","1264":"1264","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1197":"1197","1150":"1150","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","1232":"1232","1177":"1177","about 1225":"umbes 1225","Kortrijk, West Flanders, Belgium":"Kortrijk, West-Vlaanderen, Belgia","Flanders, Belgium":"Vlaanderen, Belgia"},"fi":{"1175–1232":"1175–1232","1180–1215":"1180–1215","–Male":"Kuollut","1200–Female":"1200–Kuollut","1197–1264":"1197–1264","1225–Male":"1225–Kuollut","1150–1187":"1150–1187","1145–1186":"1145–1186","1187":"1187","1264":"1264","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1197":"1197","1150":"1150","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","1232":"1232","1177":"1177","about 1225":"noin 1225","Kortrijk, West Flanders, Belgium":"Kortrijk, West-Vlaanderen, Belgia","Flanders, Belgium":"Vlaanderen, Belgia"},"fr":{"1175–1232":"1175–1232","1180–1215":"1180–1215","–Male":"Décédé","1200–Female":"1200–Décédée","1197–1264":"1197–1264","1225–Male":"1225–Décédé","1150–1187":"1150–1187","1145–1186":"1145–1186","1187":"1187","1264":"1264","1175":"1175","1186":"1186","1197":"1197","1150":"115